{"title":"Wolf Tooth GeoShift 2° Angle Headset adjusts head tube angles to the next degree","link":"https://bikerumor.com/2021/11/06/wolf-tooth-geoshift-2-angle-headset-adjusts-head-tube-angles-to-the-next-degree/","date":1636218616000,"content":"<div id=\"readability-page-1\" class=\"page\"><div><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2.jpg\" data-fancybox=\"\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2-768x512.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125010/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_2.jpg 1200w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\"></a><header></header><p>Support us! BikeRumor may earn a small commission from affiliate links in this article. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/privacy\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a>.</p></div><div role=\"main\"><article id=\"post-277673\" role=\"article\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/BlogPosting\"><section itemprop=\"text\"><p>Got a bike that you love, but wish that head tube angle was a little different? Whether steeper or slacker, sometimes it’s good to have options. And now, with the latest headset option from Wolf Tooth Components, you can choose an even more aggressive angle if that’s your thing.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth GeoShift 2° Angle Headset adjuster\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125019/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_5-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Taking the next logical step from their original <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/12/08/wolf-tooth-components-geoshift-headset-lets-you-adjust-head-angle-on-almost-any-bike/\">GeoShift headset</a>, the GeoShift 2° adds another degree to the equation. That means you can make your effective head tube angle +/-2° steeper or slacker. Like the original, the GeoShift headset actually tilts the bearing itself keeping it in line with the new angle of the steerer tube which WTC claims will result in a headset that won’t creak, bind, or have other issues typical with angle adjust headsets.</p><p>Upper assembly features:</p><ul><li>Ultralight Stem Cap With Integrated Spacer plus an aluminum bolt and a star nut</li><li>O-ring seal prevents water intrusion around the steerer tube</li><li>Custom-molded upper lip seal provides additional protection for upper bearing</li><li>Optional shim washers if needed</li></ul><p>Lower assembly features:</p><ul><li>Custom-molded dual-lip seal on the crown race to protect lower bearing in the toughest weather and trail conditions</li><li>Service and additional parts available</li></ul><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth GeoShift 2° Angle Headset \" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06125012/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset_3-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-scaled.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Wolf Tooth GeoShift 2° Angle Headset degrees\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-scaled.jpg 2560w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-297x125.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-800x338.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-120x51.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-768x324.jpg 768w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-1536x648.jpg 1536w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130108/Wolf-Tooth_GeoShift-2-Deg-Angle-Headset-compatibility-chart-2048x864.jpg 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\"></a></p><p>Sold as an upper and lower headset cup in a set, the 2° GeoShift Performance Angle Headset will be offered in ZS44/28.6 Upper &amp; ZS56/40 Lower,&nbsp; ZS44/28.6 Upper &amp; EC49/40 Lower, and ZS44/28.6 Upper &amp; EC44/40 Lower. You’ll also need to choose the right headset for your headtube length with Short (90-114mm) or Long 115-140mm.</p><p>Each complete headset is priced at $104.95 and is available now.</p><h2>Tech Specs</h2><p><strong>Weight: </strong>ZS44/28.6 Upper, ZS56/40 Lower • 92g |&nbsp;&nbsp;ZS44/28.6 Upper, ZS44/28.6 Upper, EC49/40 Lower • 107g<br><strong>Material:</strong> 6061&nbsp;aluminum<br><strong>Includes:</strong>&nbsp;Installation drifts/guides, upper and lower cups, bearings, crown race, star nut, three shims, stem cap with 5mm integrated spacer and bolt (weight listed does not include star nut, shims, or stem cap)<br><strong>Stem Cap Bolt Torque Spec:</strong>&nbsp;2-3 Nm with light grease on threads only<br><strong>Made in the USA</strong></p><h2>Steerer Tube Crown Race Adapter</h2><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3.jpg\" alt=\"Steerer Tube Crown Race Adapter&nbsp;\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130431/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_3-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6.jpg\" alt=\"Steerer Tube Crown Race Adapter&nbsp;\" width=\"1200\" height=\"800\" srcset=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6.jpg 1200w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6-297x198.jpg 297w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6-800x533.jpg 800w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6-120x80.jpg 120w, https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/06130434/Wolf-Tooth_Crown-Race-Installation-Adapter-and-Crown-Race-Adapter-1.125-to-1.5_6-768x512.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\"></a></p><p>Along with the GeoShift 2°, WTC is introducing a new line of crown race adapters to allow forks with smaller steerer tubes to use the GeoShift headsets. WTC added both a 1 1/8″ to 1 1/2″ and a 1 1/4″ to 1 1/2″ adapter. Both sell for $10.95 each.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.avantlink.com/click.php?tt=ale&amp;pw=147535&amp;mi=18985&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wolftoothcomponents.com%2Fcollections%2Fheadset-related\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"ugc\"><em>wolftoothcomponents.com</em></a></p></section></article></div></div>","author":"Zach Overholt","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"535d4f357943b26b76167c4b65935717403be29e92b7c082acdd8d78839e66e8","category":"Cycling"}